name: Whitby Abbey Ruins 2001 35mm
description: Whitby Abbey. This 35mm black and white photo was taken in 2001 with a Canon AE1. The ruins of this ancient church sits high on a hill in Whitby, England. This site inspired Bram Stoker to write Dracula after staying in Whitby in 1890. The church with its many tombstones and bats that infested it's ancient ruins gave rise to a legend.
